\tAll functions can be divided according to three criteria:
<b><i>the productive</i></b> (<b>I</b> and <b>IV</b>) and <b><i>the processional</i></b> (<b>II</b> and <b>III</b>, where <b> III </ b> is the super processional);
<b><i>the dominant</i></b> (<b>I</b> and <b>III</b>) and <b><i>the adjusting</i></b> (<b>II</b> and <b>IV</b>);
<b><i>the high</i></b> (<b>I</b> and <b>II</b>) and <b><i>the low</i></b> (<b>III</b> and <b>IV</b>).
